article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 79, Temple 76
article.story: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Antwaine Wiggins scored 17 points and College of Charleston overcame a 25-point halftime deficit to beat Temple 79-76 on Friday night in the O'Reilly Auto Parts Puerto Rico Tip-Off. The Owls (0-3) started strong, building a 12-2 lead in the first 4 1/2 minutes. Dionte Christmas scored 21 of his 31 points in the first half, helping Temple build a 50-25 lead at halftime. But Donovan Monroe hit a 3-pointer with 10:01 remaining to cap a 27-9 second-half run as the Cougars (1-2) pulled to 59-52. The Cougars shot 68 percent in the second half, including 7 of 12 3-pointers. Tony White scored 15 points for the Cougars, and Jermaine Johnson added 15. Mark Tyndale had 20 points and seven rebounds for Temple.
